 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>SCHEDULE TO </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

the Offer to Purchase Outstanding Common Stock Options Having an Exercise Price Equal to or Greater than $17.50 per Share, filed as Exhibit 99.(a)(1)(A) hereto (the &#147;Offer to Purchase&#148;), under the &#147;Summary of Terms&#148; section is
incorporated herein by reference. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>SUBJECT COMPANY INFORMATION. </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(a)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Name and Address.</B> The name of the issuer is NVIDIA Corporation, a Delaware corporation (the &#147;Company&#148; or &#147;NVIDIA&#148;). The address of its principal executive
office is 2701 San Tomas Expressway, Santa Clara, California 95050. The telephone number of its principal executive office is (408)&nbsp;486-2000. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(b)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Securities.</B> This Tender Offer Statement on Schedule TO relates to the Offer to Purchase by the Company to purchase currently outstanding options having an exercise price
equal to or greater than $17.50 per share and granted under the Company&#146;s 2007 Equity Incentive Plan, 2000 Nonstatutory Equity Incentive Plan, or 1998 Equity Incentive Plan, or granted under the PortalPlayer, Inc. Amended and Restated 2004
Stock Incentive Plan and PortalPlayer, Inc. 1999 Stock Option Plan and assumed by the Company in connection with its acquisition of PortalPlayer, Inc. (the &#147;Offer&#148;). Only employees of NVIDIA or one of its subsidiaries as of
February&nbsp;11, 2009 who continue to be employees through March&nbsp;11, 2009, or a later date if the Offer period is extended, are eligible to participate in the Offer. Employees who are currently on medical, maternity, worker&#146;s
compensation, military or other statutorily protected leave of absence, or a personal leave of absence, are eligible to participate in the Offer. Notwithstanding the foregoing, any outstanding options that have been amended to comply with Internal
Revenue Code Section&nbsp;409A are not subject to the Offer. In addition, all members of the Company&#146;s Board of Directors and the officers of the Company who file reports under Section&nbsp;16(a) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 are not
eligible to participate in this Offer. The information set forth in the Offer to Purchase under the &#147;Summary of Terms&#148; section and Section&nbsp;1 (&#147;Eligible Participants; Number of Options; Offer Termination Date&#148;) is
incorporated herein by reference. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Exhibit 99.(a)(1)(A) </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="font-size:150px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:0px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;border-bottom:0.5pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P

FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>NVIDIA CORPORATION </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>2701 SAN TOMAS EXPRESSWAY </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>SANTA CLARA, CALIFORNIA 95050 </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>(408)
486-2000 </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>OFFER TO PURCHASE OUTSTANDING </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>COMMON STOCK OPTIONS HAVING AN EXERCISE PRICE </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>EQUAL TO OR GREATER THAN $17.50 PER SHARE
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>FEBRUARY 11, 2009 </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:60px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P
STYLE="line-height:0px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;border-bottom:0.5pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:0.5pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" COLOR="#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>NVIDIA CORPORATION </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>OFFER TO PURCHASE OUTSTANDING COMMON STOCK OPTIONS HAVING AN </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>EXERCISE PRICE EQUAL TO OR GREATER
THAN $17.50 PER SHARE </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>THE OFFER EXPIRES AT MIDNIGHT, PACIFIC TIME, ON </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"
ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>WEDNESDAY, MARCH 11, 2009, UNLESS THE OFFER PERIOD IS EXTENDED </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">NVIDIA
Corporation (the &#147;Company&#148; or &#147;NVIDIA&#148;) is offering, for compensatory purposes, to purchase from eligible employees of NVIDIA and its subsidiaries certain outstanding stock options for a cash payment, payable as described in the
materials that follow (the &#147;Offer&#148;). Only vested and unvested outstanding options to purchase shares of NVIDIA common stock (&#147;Common Stock&#148;) granted under the Company&#146;s equity incentive plans or assumed in connection with
its acquisition of PortalPlayer that have an exercise price equal to or greater than $17.50 per share are eligible to be tendered for a cash payment in the Offer (each, an &#147;Eligible Option,&#148; and collectively, &#147;Eligible Options&#148;).
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The amount that we are offering to pay for the cancellation of each option share under the Offer is: </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">$3.00 for Eligible Options with exercise prices less than $28.00 per share (but not less than $17.50 per share); and </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">$2.00 for Eligible Options with exercise prices of $28.00 per share or higher. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">NVIDIA evaluated the amount it is offering to pay using the Black-Scholes option pricing model, as further described under Section&nbsp;3 of this document. All payments will be reduced by applicable income taxes,
social insurance contributions, payroll taxes and any other taxes that are required to be withheld (referred to throughout this document as &#147;tax withholdings&#148;). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Participation in the Offer is voluntary.</B> If you wish to participate in the Offer, you must: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">properly complete and submit your election via the website or by paper to participate in the Offer during the period beginning on February&nbsp;11, 2009 and ending
at midnight, Pacific Time, on March&nbsp;11, 2009 (i.e., the end of the day on March&nbsp;11, 2009), or a later date if the Offer period is extended; and </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">be an employee of NVIDIA or one of its subsidiaries (excluding all members of our Board of Directors and our officers who file reports under Section&nbsp;16(a) of
the Securities Exchange Act of 1934) throughout the period described in the prior bullet (an &#147;Eligible Participant&#148;). </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">See
below for information on how to complete your election to participate. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We are making the Offer upon the terms and subject to the
conditions described in this document, including the conditions described in Section&nbsp;7 of this document. We will assess whether we are permitted to make the Offer in all jurisdictions. In the event that we determine that we are not legally able
to make the Offer in a particular jurisdiction, we reserve the right to withdraw the Offer in that particular jurisdiction. If we withdraw the Offer in a particular jurisdiction, the Offer will not be made to, nor will Eligible Options be accepted
for payment under the terms of the Offer from or on behalf of employees in that jurisdiction. However, we may, at our discretion, take any actions necessary for us to make the Offer legally available to eligible employees in any jurisdiction.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Participating in the Offer involves risks. See &#147;The Offer&#151;Material Risks of Participating In the Offer&#148; beginning on
page 7. </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Although our Board of Directors has approved the Offer, neither we nor our Board of Directors make any recommendation as to
whether or not you should tender one or more of your Eligible Options under the Offer. You must make your own decision whether to tender your Eligible Options. You should carefully review this document in its entirety before deciding to participate
in the Offer. </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">i </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Shares of our Common Stock are listed on the NASDAQ Global Select Market under the symbol
&#147;NVDA.&#148; On February&nbsp;10, 2009, the closing price of our Common Stock as reported on the NASDAQ Global Select Market was $9.32 per share. You should obtain current market prices for our Common Stock before you decide to participate in
the Offer. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">You should direct questions about the Offer, requests for assistance in completing the related documents and requests for
additional copies of this document or related documents from Stock Administration by sending an email to tenderoffer@nvidia.com or by calling (408)&nbsp;486-2029. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>This transaction has not been approved or disapproved by the Securities and Exchange Commission (&#147;SEC&#148;) or any state securities commission nor has the SEC or any state securities commission passed upon
the fairness or merits of such transaction or upon the accuracy or adequacy of the information contained in this document. Any representation to the contrary is a criminal offense. In the event of any conflict between this documentation and the
rules of the participating plans or any applicable legislation, the rules or legislation (as the case may be) will take precedence. All information regarding taxation consequences is general information only and does not consider particular
individual circumstances. We recommend that you consult with your tax advisor to determine the tax consequences of electing to participate in the Offer. </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>IMPORTANT&#151;STEPS YOU MUST TAKE TO PARTICIPATE </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">If you would like to accept the Offer, you must
properly complete and submit your election to the Company through the Company&#146;s secured offer website at <I>https://nvidia.equitybenefits.com/</I> (the &#147;Offer Website&#148;). We will make computer and Internet access available at our
office locations to any Eligible Participant who does not have Internet access. If you are not able to submit your election electronically via the Offer Website as a result of technical failures of the Offer Website, such as the Offer Website being
unavailable or the Offer Website not accepting your election, you must complete and sign a paper election form for all of your Eligible Options and fax your election form to (408)&nbsp;486-2577. To obtain a paper election form, please contact Stock
Administration at tenderoffer@nvidia.com or by calling (408)&nbsp;486-2029. Your election must be received by the Company before midnight, Pacific Time, on March&nbsp;11, 2009 (or a later expiration date if we extend the Offer). Elections not made
via the Offer Website or received by NVIDIA by midnight on March&nbsp;11, 2009, even if sent prior to the Offer expiration time, will be disregarded. Accordingly, please allow time for delivery when sending your paper election form(s). If we do not
receive your election by the Offer expiration time, you will be deemed to have rejected the Offer. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">If you accept the Offer and our stock
price increases above the exercise price of your Eligible Options during the term of your Eligible Options, the value of the consideration you receive may be less than the value of the Common Stock you would have received upon exercise of your
Eligible Options. <B><I>Therefore, we cannot guarantee that the total consideration you receive will be higher than what you would receive if you do not tender your Eligible Options under the Offer. </I></B>NVIDIA and its Board of Directors
recognize that the decision to accept or reject the Offer is an individual one that should be based on a variety of factors, and you should consult your personal advisors about your financial or tax situation. The information about the Offer from
NVIDIA is limited to the contents of this document. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We have not authorized any person to make any recommendation on our behalf as to
whether or not you should tender your Eligible Options. We have not authorized anyone to give you any information or to make any representation in connection with the Offer other than the information and representations contained in this document
and all related documents included as part of the Tender Offer Statement on Schedule TO filed with the SEC on February&nbsp;11, 2009. If anyone makes any such recommendation or representation to you or gives you any such information, you must not
rely upon that recommendation, representation or information as having been authorized by NVIDIA. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">iii </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" COLOR="#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="otprom47158_1"></A>SUMMARY OF TERMS </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The following are answers to some of the questions that you may have about NVIDIA Corporation&#146;s offer to purchase from eligible employees of NVIDIA
Corporation and its subsidiaries certain outstanding option grants, whether or not vested, granted under its equity incentive plans or assumed in connection with a business acquisition (the &#147;Offer&#148;), on the terms described in this
document. We urge you to carefully read the remainder of this document and the accompanying documents because the information in this summary is not complete. We have included references to the relevant sections of this document where you can find a
more complete description of the topics in this summary. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Questions Related to How the Option Repurchase Works </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Q1:</I></B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>What is the Offer?</I></B> </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We are offering to
purchase any and all Eligible Options (as described in Q5 below) you hold for a cash payment for each option share. The amount before applicable tax withholdings that we are offering to pay for the cancellation of each option share under the Offer
(the &#147;Per Option Amount&#148;) is: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">$3.00 for Eligible Options with exercise prices less than $28.00 per share (but not less than $17.50 per share); and </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">$2.00 for Eligible Options with exercise prices of $28.00 per share or higher. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Participation in the Offer is voluntary. </B>If you wish to participate in the Offer, you must: </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">submit your election to tender Eligible Options through our secured offer website (the &#147;Offer Website&#148;) at <I>https://nvidia.equitybenefits.com/</I> or,
if necessary, by the paper-based method described in Q20; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">properly complete your election in the manner described in the prior bullet, during the period beginning on February&nbsp;11, 2009 and ending at midnight, Pacific
Time, on March&nbsp;11, 2009 (i.e., the end of the day on March&nbsp;11, 2009), or a later date if the Offer period is extended (the latest such date and time, the &#147;Offer Termination Date&#148;); and </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">qualify as an &#147;Eligible Participant&#148; (as described in Q3), which generally means you are employed by us continuously throughout the period described in
the prior bullet. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Q2:</I></B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Why is NVIDIA making the Offer?</I></B> </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">NVIDIA uses
equity to promote employee retention and provide an incentive vehicle valued by employees that is also aligned to shareholder interest. However, our stock price has declined significantly over the past year, and all of your Eligible Options are
&#147;out-of-the-money&#148; (i.e., have exercise prices above our current stock price). We are providing you with the opportunity to obtain a cash payment for certain grants that are &#147;out-of-the-money&#148;. Whether or not you choose to
participate in the Offer is your decision. You are free to not participate in the Offer if you so choose. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Q3:</I></B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Who can participate in the Offer?</I></B> </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Only
Eligible Participants may participate in the Offer. &#147;Eligible Participants&#148; are employees of NVIDIA and its subsidiaries as of February&nbsp;11, 2009, and who continue to be employees of NVIDIA or its subsidiaries through March&nbsp;11,
2009, or a later date if the Offer period is extended, that hold Eligible Options. If you are currently on medical, maternity, workers&#146; compensation, military or other statutorily protected leave of absence or a personal leave of absence, you
are also eligible to participate in the Offer. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">1 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" COLOR="#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Q4:</I></B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Who is not eligible to participate in the Offer? </I></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">Employees who resign or are terminated at any time before the termination of the Offer are not eligible. In addition, none of the non-employee members of our Board of Directors or our officers who file reports under Section&nbsp;16(a) of
the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 are eligible to participate in the Offer. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Q5:</I></B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>What options may be tendered for a cash payment in the Offer? </I></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">All vested and unvested outstanding options to purchase shares of our Common Stock that have exercise prices equal to or greater than $17.50 per share are eligible. This includes stock options currently outstanding
under our equity incentive plans and assumed in connection with the acquisition of PortalPlayer. However, any outstanding options that have been amended to comply with Internal Revenue Code Section&nbsp;409A are not Eligible Options. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Q6:</I></B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Do I have to tender all of my Eligible Options or can I just tender some of them? </I></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">If you hold different Eligible Option grants, you may choose to tender some, all or none of these grants. However, if you choose to tender any particular
grant of an Eligible Option, you must tender <B>all </B>option shares subject to that grant. For example, if you have an option grant for 4,500 shares with an exercise price of $25.00 per share, you must tender all 4,500 option shares. You may not
tender to NVIDIA 2,500 of the 4,500 option shares (and retain 2,000 option shares). Any stock options you hold that are not Eligible Options, as well as any Eligible Options you choose not to tender, will remain outstanding under their existing
terms and conditions. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Q7:</I></B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>What if my options are unvested? </I></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Both the
vested and unvested portion of your Eligible Options may be tendered in the Offer. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Q8:</I></B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>What amount of consideration will I receive if I tender my Eligible Options? </I></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The amount we will pay you (before applicable tax withholdings) under the Offer is determined upon the Offer Termination Date by summing the total cash
value of each Eligible Option (i.e., the Per Option Amount multiplied by the number of option shares) that you have tendered (the &#147;Total Payment&#148;). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">For example, if you have an option grant for 2,000 shares with an exercise price of $30.00 per share and an option grant for 1,000 shares with an exercise price of $17.95 per share, and you tender those options under
the Offer, you will receive $7,000 (i.e., 1,000 x $3.00 plus 2,000 x $2.00), less applicable tax withholdings. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Your Eligible Options and
the Total Payment can be found on the Offer Website at <I>https://nvidia.equitybenefits.com/.</I> </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Q9:</I></B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>If I participate in the Offer, what will happen to the Eligible Options that I tender? </I></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Immediately following the Offer Termination Date, we will cancel all of your Eligible Options that have been properly tendered in exchange for the prompt
lump sum cash payment equal to the Total Payment, less applicable tax withholdings. You will no longer have any rights or obligations with respect to any Eligible Options that are cancelled. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Q10:</I></B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>If I participate in the Offer, how and when will I receive my cash payment? </I></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Promptly following the termination of the Offer and our purchase of the Eligible Options, you will receive a single lump sum cash payment equal to the Total Payment, less applicable tax withholdings and without
interest. Payment will be made on or before the first administratively practicable payroll date following the scheduled termination of the Offer (but in no event later than March&nbsp;25, 2009) (the &#147;Payment Date&#148;). </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">2 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" COLOR="#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Q11:</I></B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>How was the amount of my Total Payment determined? </I></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">The Per Option Amount that we will pay under the Offer is based on our valuation of the Eligible Options using the Black-Scholes option pricing model, a widely-used method of valuing stock options. This pricing model takes into
consideration numerous factors, including our stock price, the expected stock price volatility of the underlying stock, the exercise price of any Eligible Option, the Company&#146;s risk free interest rate, the expected dividend yield and the
expected term of each Eligible Option. You must make your own determination of the value to you of your Eligible Options, and you should consult with your personal advisors if you have questions about your financial or tax situation. For a more
detailed explanation of the Black-Scholes option pricing model and other additional information regarding our determination of the Per Option Amount, see the next question and Section&nbsp;3 of this document. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Q12:</I></B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>What should I consider before participating in the Offer? </I></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">If you participate in the Offer, the Total Payment, less applicable tax withholdings, you receive under the Offer may or may not be more valuable to you than continuing to hold your Eligible Options in the future.
This determination depends on a number of factors, including the Eligible Option exercise price, the Eligible Option expiration date, stock price performance and the timing of any fluctuations regarding the trading of our Common Stock. To illustrate
this, consider the following hypothetical scenarios: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Assume that you hold an Eligible Option covering 1,000 option shares with an exercise
price of $32 per share at a time when our Common Stock is trading at $7 per share. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">If our stock price were to stay below $32 per share, your Eligible Option would have no cash value to you because it would still be out-of-the-money. Under these
circumstances, your Eligible Option would have less cash value than the $2,000 cash payment, before applicable tax withholdings, that you would be eligible to receive by participating in the Offer. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">If our stock price were to rise to $33 per share, your Eligible Option would now be $1 in-the-money, resulting in an aggregate value of $1,000 (i.e., the result
obtained by multiplying $1 (representing the excess of the market price of $33 over the exercise price of $32) by 1,000 (the number of option shares in this example)). Under these circumstances, although your Eligible Option would be in-the-money,
the $2,000 cash payment, before applicable tax withholdings, that you would be eligible to receive by participating in the Offer would be higher than the amount the Eligible Option was in-the-money. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">If our stock price were to rise to $37 per share, each option share would be $5 in-the-money, resulting in an aggregate cash value of $5,000 (i.e., the result
obtained by multiplying $5 (representing the excess of the market price of $37 over the exercise price of $32) by 1,000 (the number of option shares in this example)). Under these circumstances, the $2,000 cash payment, before applicable tax
withholdings, that you would be eligible to receive by participating in the Offer would be less than the amount the Eligible Option was in-the-money. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In evaluating the Offer, you should keep in mind that the future performance of our stock price and the value of your Eligible Option(s) will depend upon, among other factors, the overall economic environment, the
performance of the overall stock market and companies in our industry and the performance of our own business. Accordingly, there are risks associated with keeping your Eligible Options and deciding not to participate in the Offer. Participating in
the Offer also involves risks, including the risk that our stock price could increase in the future. If our stock price rises above the exercise price of your tendered Eligible Options, those Eligible Options might have been worth more than the
Total Payment that you receive in exchange for them. Please also note any payment you receive for tendering your Eligible Options will be reduced by applicable tax withholdings. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">For more information about the risks relating to participation in the Offer, see &#147;The Offer&#151;Material Risks of Participating In the Offer&#148;
beginning on page&nbsp;7. We also recommend that you read the discussion about </FONT>
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">3 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" COLOR="#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%">
<FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">our business contained in the &#147;Management&#146;s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations&#148; section of our most
recent Annual Report on Form 10-K, as well as our Quarterly Report on Form 10-Q for the period ended October&nbsp;26, 2008. See Section&nbsp;17 of this document. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Q13:</I></B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>If I am an Eligible Participant located outside of the United States who holds Eligible Options, am I subject to the same terms as described in this Offer?
</I></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Yes. Non-U.S. employees should also refer to Appendix A of this document, &#147;Guide to Non-U.S. Issues,&#148; for a
discussion of the tax and other consequences of accepting or rejecting the Offer under the law of the country in which you are located. NVIDIA (or one of its subsidiaries, as applicable) will assess its requirements with respect to tax withholdings
on the Total Payment, and where appropriate, will withhold and/or report applicable income taxes, social insurance contributions, payroll taxes and other taxes as required. Regardless of withholding, you are responsible for reporting and paying all
taxes and social insurance contributions arising from your election to tender Eligible Options in the Offer. Payment will be made in your local currency, using the currency exchange rate in effect on the Offer Termination Date. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Q14:</I></B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>What if I do not accept the Offer? </I></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">If you
do not accept the Offer, you will keep your Eligible Options and you will not receive any cash payment. No changes will be made to the terms and conditions of your Eligible Options, and they will remain outstanding. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Q15:</I></B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>How does the Offer affect my 401(k), ESPP, or other benefits? </I></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The payment you may receive will not be considered part of normal or expected compensation or salary for purposes of calculating any severance, resignation, termination, redundancy, end of service payments, bonuses,
overtime, long-service awards, pension or retirement benefits or similar payments, or for purposes of our 401(k) plan, our employee stock purchase plan or any other plans we provide or make available to you. For example, no portion of any payment
you receive under the Offer will be contributed to your 401(k) or fund or otherwise affect your ability to make purchases under the 1998 Employee Stock Purchase Plan Offering, as amended. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Q16:</I></B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Does my participation in the Offer affect my eligibility to receive future equity award grants? </I></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Your participation will have no impact on either your eligibility to receive future equity grants from NVIDIA or the number of future equity awards you
might receive from NVIDIA. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Q17:</I></B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Will I have to pay taxes if I tender my Eligible Options in the Offer? </I></B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Yes. Any applicable income taxes, social insurance contributions, payroll taxes and other taxes due on the payments you receive under the Offer will be withheld from the amount you receive on the Payment Date and paid
to the appropriate taxing authority, to the extent required by law. For U.S. employees, the receipt of payments under the Offer will be treated as ordinary income and NVIDIA will be required to withhold certain taxes. If you are an employee located
outside the U.S., the income taxes, social insurance contributions, payroll taxes and other taxes required to be withheld will depend on the jurisdiction. NVIDIA (or one of its subsidiaries, as appropriate) will assess its withholding requirements
on the Total Payment (and/or your acceptance of the Offer), and where appropriate, will make withholdings. Regardless of withholding, you are responsible for reporting and paying all taxes and social insurance contributions arising from your
election to tender Eligible Options in the Offer. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">BEFORE ACCEPTING THE OFFER, WE RECOMMEND THAT YOU CONSULT WITH YOUR TAX ADVISOR TO
DETERMINE THE TAX AND SOCIAL CONTRIBUTION CONSEQUENCES OF ELECTING TO PARTICIPATE IN THE OFFER UNDER THE LAWS OF THE COUNTRY IN WHICH YOU LIVE AND WORK, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO A DETERMINATION OF WHETHER TAXES IN ADDITION TO THE AMOUNTS
WITHHELD FROM YOUR PAYMENTS UNDER THE OFFER, IF ANY, WILL BE DUE AS A RESULT OF ELECTING TO PARTICIPATE IN THE OFFER. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

before midnight, Pacific Time, on March&nbsp;11, 2009 (or, if we extend the Offer period, a later date). Elections not made via the Offer Website or received by NVIDIA before midnight on March&nbsp;11, 2009, even if sent prior to the Offer
expiration time, will be disregarded. Accordingly, please allow time for delivery when sending your paper election form(s). If we do not receive your election by the Offer expiration time, you will be deemed to have rejected the Offer. </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">To change or withdraw your election to tender your Eligible Options in the Offer, you must go to the
Offer Website at <I>https://nvidia.equitybenefits.com/</I> and change your election to participate. If you are not able to submit your revised election electronically via the Offer Website as a result of technical failures of the Offer Website, such
as the Offer Website being unavailable or the Offer Website not accepting your revised election, you must complete and sign a paper change/withdrawal form and fax your withdrawal form to (408)&nbsp;486-2577. To obtain a paper change/withdrawal form,
please contact Stock Administration by sending an email to tenderoffer@nvidia.com or by calling (408)&nbsp;486-2029. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:5%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We must receive your
change in election or withdrawal before midnight, Pacific Time, on March&nbsp;11, 2009 (or, if we extend the Offer period, a later date). Changes or withdrawals not made via the Offer Website or received by NVIDIA before midnight, Pacific Time, on
March&nbsp;11, 2009, even if sent prior to the Offer expiration time, will be disregarded. Accordingly, please allow time for delivery when sending your paper change/withdrawal form(s). If we do not receive your election before the Offer expires,
you will be deemed to have rejected the Offer. However, if, after forty (40)&nbsp;business days from the commencement of the Offer, we have not accepted for payment all Eligible Options you elected to tender, you may withdraw any Eligible Options
you elected to tender pursuant to the Offer. See Section&nbsp;5 of this document. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="otprom47158_2"></A>THE OFFER </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="otprom47158_3"></A>Material Risks of Participating In the Offer </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Participation in this Offer involves a number of potential risks, including the material risks described below. Eligible Participants should carefully consider these risks and are urged to speak with an investment and
tax advisor as necessary before deciding whether or not to participate in this Offer. In addition, we strongly encourage you to read this document in its entirety and review the documents referred to in Section&nbsp;17 (and, for Non-U.S. employees,
Section&nbsp;13 and Appendix A) of this document. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>If our stock price increases after the date that your tendered Eligible Options are cancelled,
your cancelled Eligible Options might have been worth more than the cash payment you receive in exchange for them. </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Although our
stock price is currently lower than the exercise price of the Eligible Options you may tender in this Offer, our stock price may increase in the future. If you accept the Offer and our stock price increases above the exercise price of your Eligible
Options during the term of your Eligible Options, the value of your Total Payment under the Offer may be less than the value of the Common Stock you would have received upon exercise of your Eligible Options. <B>Therefore, we cannot guarantee that
the value of your Total Payment under the Offer will be higher than what you would receive if you do not tender your Eligible Options under the Offer</B>. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2"><B><I>The Per Option Amount to be paid in the Offer may not accurately reflect the value of your Eligible Options at the Offer Termination Date. </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The calculation of the Per Option Amount was based on the Black-Scholes option pricing model, a widely-used valuation model and relied on numerous assumptions. If a different model or different assumptions had been
used, the amount to have been paid in the Offer for Eligible Options may have varied from the applicable Per Option Amount reflected in the Offer. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">NVIDIA and our Board of Directors recognize that the decision to accept or reject the Offer is an individual one that should be based on a variety of factors, and you should consult your personal advisors if you have questions about your
financial or tax situation. The information about this Offer that is available from NVIDIA is limited solely to the information contained in this document. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">7 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="otprom47158_4"></A>1.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>ELIGIBLE PARTICIPANTS; NUMBER OF OPTIONS; OFFER TERMINATION DATE. </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We are offering to purchase for cash Eligible Options (as defined below) held by Eligible Participants (as defined below), on the terms described in this document. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#147;Eligible Participants&#148; are employees of NVIDIA and its subsidiaries as of February&nbsp;11, 2009, who continue to be employees through the
Offer Termination Date (as defined below). If you are currently on medical, maternity, workers&#146; compensation, military or other statutorily protected leave of absence or a &#147;personal&#148; leave of absence, you are also eligible to
participate in the Offer. Employees who resign or are terminated at any time before the termination of the Offer are not eligible to participate in the Offer. In addition, none of the non-employee members of our Board of Directors or our officers
who file reports under Section&nbsp;16(a) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 (&#147;Section 16&#148;) are eligible to participate in the Offer. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">&#147;Eligible Options&#148; consist of options with exercise prices equal to or greater than $17.50 per share that have been granted under our 2007 Equity Incentive Plan, 2000 Nonstatutory Equity Incentive Plan and 1998 Equity Incentive
Plan and granted under the PortalPlayer, Inc. Amended and Restated 2004 Stock Incentive Plan and PortalPlayer, Inc. 1999 Stock Option Plan and assumed by us in connection with our acquisition of PortalPlayer, Inc. (collectively, the
&#147;Participating Plans&#148;). Notwithstanding the foregoing, any outstanding options that have been amended to comply with Internal Revenue Code Section&nbsp;409A are not Eligible Options. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">If a vested stock option that you hold expires, terminates or is forfeited before the Offer Termination Date, whether because of termination of your
employment, expiration of the option in accordance with its terms or otherwise, that stock option will not be an Eligible Option. Likewise, unvested stock options that expire, terminate or are forfeited before the Offer Termination Date, either
because of termination of your employment or otherwise, will not be Eligible Options. Only stock options that have not expired, terminated or been forfeited, whether vested or unvested, and that remain outstanding on the Offer Termination Date, will
be Eligible Options. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">If you hold more than one option grant, you may tender as many or as few of your option grants that qualify as
Eligible Options. If you elect to tender an Eligible Option pursuant to the Offer, you must tender all of the outstanding shares under that Eligible Option. You will not be allowed to tender a portion of an option grant that qualifies as an Eligible
Option. If you do not elect to tender an Eligible Option, such Eligible Option will not be purchased by NVIDIA and will continue on its current terms. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">As of January&nbsp;25, 2009, options to purchase 97,086,780 shares of Common Stock were outstanding under the Participating Plans. The options had exercise prices of between $0.83 and $1,249.65 per share. Of these
options, options to purchase 36,254,868 shares of our Common Stock had an exercise price equal to or greater than $17.50, of which 33,109,990 shares are held by Eligible Participants. The shares of Common Stock issuable upon exercise of Eligible
Options held by Eligible Participants represent approximately 34.1% of the total shares of Common Stock issuable upon exercise of all options outstanding under the Participating Plans as of January&nbsp;25, 2009. As of January&nbsp;25, 2009, other
than 367,500 options outstanding under the 1998 Non-Employee Directors Stock Option Plan, there were no other options to purchase shares of our Common Stock outstanding. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our Offer is subject to the terms and conditions described in this document. We will only accept Eligible Options that are properly tendered for purchase under the Offer and not validly withdrawn in accordance with
Sections 4 and 5 of this document before the Offer expires on the Offer Termination Date. We may, however, reject any or all elections, withdrawals or tenders of Eligible Options to the extent that we determine the election or withdrawal is not
properly completed or to the extent that we determine it is unlawful to accept any of the Eligible Options you elect to tender or to the extent certain conditions described in this document exist which in our reasonable judgment makes it inadvisable
to proceed with the Offer. See Sections 6 and 7 of this document. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The term &#147;Offer Termination Date&#148; for this Offer means
midnight, Pacific Time, on March&nbsp;11, 2009, unless and until we, in our discretion or as required, extend the period of time during which the Offer will remain open. </FONT>
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

at which the Offer expires. See Section&nbsp;14 of this document for a description of our rights to extend, postpone, terminate and/or amend the Offer or to reject any Eligible Option that you elect to exchange. </FONT></P> <P

the Offer is scheduled to expire within ten (10)&nbsp;business days from the date we notify you of such action, we also intend to extend the Offer until ten (10)&nbsp;business days after the date the notice is published. </FONT></P> <P

STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A &#147;business day&#148; means any day other than a Saturday, Sunday or federal holiday in the United States and consists of the time period from 12:01
a.m. through 12:00 midnight, Eastern Time. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="otprom47158_5"></A>2.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>PURPOSE OF THE OFFER. </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">NVIDIA uses equity to
promote employee retention and provide an incentive vehicle valued by employees that is also aligned to stockholder interest. However, our stock price has declined significantly over the past year, and all of your Eligible Options are
&#147;out-of-the-money&#148; (i.e., have exercise prices above our stock price). We are providing you with the opportunity to obtain a cash payment for Eligible Options. Whether or not you choose to participate in the Offer is your decision. You are
free to not participate in the Offer if you so choose. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Also, the Offer may increase the number of shares available for issuance under our
2007 Equity Incentive Plan. To the extent Eligible Options granted under the Participating Plans (other than the options assumed by us in connection with our acquisition of PortalPlayer, Inc.) are tendered by you and purchased by us in the Offer,
the number of shares available for issuance under our 2007 Equity Incentive Plan will increase by the number of shares subject to the Eligible Options tendered in this Offer. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="otprom47158_6"></A>3.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>VALUATION OF ELIGIBLE OPTIONS; AMOUNT OF THE PAYMENT FOR ELIGIBLE OPTIONS. </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Consideration.</B> Eligible Participants who participate in the Offer will receive, in exchange for the cancellation of their Eligible Options, a cash payment for each option share. The amount before applicable tax
withholdings that we are offering to pay for the cancellation of each option share under the Offer (the &#147;Per Option Amount&#148;) is: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">$3.00 for Eligible Options with exercise prices less than $28.00 per share (but not less than $17.50 per share); and </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">$2.00 for Eligible Options with exercise prices of $28.00 per share or higher. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The actual amount you will receive under the Offer will be determined upon the Offer Termination Date by: </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">summing the total cash value of each Eligible Option (i.e., the Per Option Amount multiplied by the number of option shares) that you have tendered (the &#147;Total
Payment&#148;); and </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">subtracting applicable tax withholdings. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">9 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">For example, if you have an option grant for 2,000 shares with an exercise price of $30.00 per share and
an option grant for 1,000 shares with an exercise price of $17.95 per share, and you tender those options under the Offer, you will receive $7,000 (i.e., 1,000 x $3.00 plus 2,000 x $2.00), less applicable tax withholdings. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Applicable tax withholdings or charges will be withheld from the Total Payment and paid by us (or one of our subsidiaries, as appropriate) to the
applicable taxing authority, to the extent required by law. If you are a Non-U.S. employee, the tax withholdings will depend on the laws in your jurisdiction. Eligible Participants should consult with their tax advisor to determine if additional
taxes will be due. Depending on your personal tax situation, you may owe taxes on the Total Payment above and beyond the amounts withheld and such amounts are your responsibility to pay. Any failure to timely remit the proper amount of taxes may
result in tax penalties, which will be your responsibility to pay. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Your Eligible Options, the Total Payment and the total cash payment
before tax withholdings for each Eligible Option that you elect to tender under the Offer, can be found on our secure Offer Website at <I>https://nvidia.equitybenefits.com/</I>. Please note that, as explained herein, this amount will be reduced by
applicable tax withholding. Also, if you are an employee located outside the U.S., the Total Payment will be converted from U.S. dollars to local currency on the day the Offer Termination Date. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Valuation.</B> In determining the Per Option Amount, NVIDIA valued the Eligible Options using the Black-Scholes option pricing model. The
Black-Scholes model is an established and commonly used method for valuing stock options and uses the following factors: stock price, the exercise price of the stock option, the Company&#146;s risk-free interest rate, the expected volatility of the
underlying stock, the expected dividend yield of the stock and the expected life of the stock option. Some of these inputs are objectively determinable, while others, such as appropriate volatility measures, require some judgment. For purposes of
this calculation, NVIDIA considered the following measures: <B> </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Stock price: closing stock price, the 10-day historical average closing stock price and 20-day historical average closing stock price, which as of February&nbsp;10,
2009 were $9.32, $8.89 and $8.29, respectively; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Exercise price: $17.50 and $28.00 per share; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Expected life of stock option: 5 years, which is approximately the remaining contractual life of the Eligible Options; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Risk-free interest rate: 1.6% based on the rate from the zero-coupon yield curve derived from the U.S. Treasury Strips yield table; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Expected volatility: 60%, the approximate volatility of our Common Stock over the last five years; and </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Expected dividend yield: 0%. We have never paid and do not expect to pay cash dividends for the foreseeable future. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">You must make your own determination of the value to you of your Eligible Options, and you should consult with your personal advisors if you have
questions about your financial or tax situation. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="otprom47158_7"></A>4.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>PROCEDURES FOR TENDERING YOUR ELIGIBLE OPTIONS. </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">You may tender your stock options only as described in this Section&nbsp;4. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Making Your Election.</B> To participate in the
Offer, you must tender Eligible Options before the Offer Termination Date. To tender your Eligible Options, you must go online to the Offer Website <I>https://nvidia.equitybenefits.com/</I> and complete an online election form to confirm your
election to participate in the Offer. We will make computer and Internet access available at our office locations to any Eligible Participant who does not have Internet access. If you are not able to submit your election electronically via the Offer
Website as a result of technical failures of the Offer Website, such as the Offer Website being unavailable or the </FONT>
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">10 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" COLOR="#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">
<FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Offer Website not accepting your election, you must complete and sign a paper election form for all of your Eligible Options and deliver or fax your election
form to (408)&nbsp;486-2577. To obtain a paper election form, please contact Stock Administration by sending an email to tenderoffer@nvidia.com or by calling (408)&nbsp;486-2029. If you do not submit your election before 12:00 midnight, Pacific
Time, on March&nbsp;11, 2009 (or, if we extend the Offer period, a later date we will specify), your tender of Eligible Options will not be given effect. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">If you elect to tender an Eligible Option pursuant to the Offer, you must tender all of the outstanding shares under the Eligible Option. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">For your election to participate in the Offer to be valid, you must make your election by 12:00 midnight, Pacific Time, on March&nbsp;11, 2009 (or, if we extend the Offer, a later date will be specified). If you do
not make any election, you will not participate in the Offer, and all Eligible Options you currently hold and any stock options you hold that are not Eligible Options will remain outstanding under their existing terms and conditions. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">You do not need to return the stock option agreements for your Eligible Options, if you have them, to effectively elect to accept the Offer, as they will
be automatically cancelled if NVIDIA accepts your Eligible Options for purchase pursuant to the Offer. However, you will be required to return your stock option agreements upon NVIDIA&#146;s request. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Determination of Validity; Rejection of Options; Waiver of Defects; No Obligation to Give Notice of Defects.</B> We will determine, in our discretion,
all questions as to the number of shares subject to Eligible Options and the validity, form, eligibility (including time of receipt) and acceptance of any tender of Eligible Options. Our determinations regarding these matters will be final and
binding on all parties. We may reject any or all tenders of Eligible Options to the extent that we determine the election is not properly completed or to the extent that we determine it is unlawful to accept any of the Eligible Options that you
elect to tender. We may waive any or all of the conditions of the Offer for all Eligible Participants. We may waive any defect or irregularity in any election with respect to any particular Eligible Option or any particular Eligible Participant, in
each case in our sole discretion. No Eligible Options will be accepted for purchase under the Offer until all defects or irregularities have been cured by the Eligible Participants tendering the Eligible Options or waived by us. Neither we nor any
other person is obligated to give notice of receipt of any election or of any defects or irregularities involved in the election to tender any Eligible Options pursuant to the Offer, and no one will be liable for failing to give notice of receipt of
any election or of any such defects or irregularities. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Our Acceptance Constitutes an Agreement.</B> If you elect to tender your
Eligible Options according to the procedures described above, you will have accepted the terms and conditions of the Offer. Our acceptance of Eligible Options that are properly tendered for purchase under the Offer will form a binding agreement
between you and us on the terms and subject to the conditions of this Offer. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We currently expect that we will accept promptly after the
Offer Termination Date all properly and timely made elections to tender Eligible Options for purchase under the Offer that have not been validly withdrawn prior to the Offer Termination Date. We reserve the right to extend; terminate; postpone
and/or amend the Offer; or reject the Eligible Options you elect to tender pursuant to the Offer. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
